WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.044 --> 00:00:04.170
<i>One of the most important skills
doctors learn</i>

2
00:00:04.171 --> 00:00:06.130
<i>is how to keep their emotions in check.</i>

3
00:00:06.131 --> 00:00:08.049
<i>We call this skill "doctor face."</i>

4
00:00:08.050 --> 00:00:11.093
So. during your son's surgery.
we found a tumor.

5
00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:12.220
I'm so sorry.

6
00:00:14.139 --> 00:00:17.184
<i>I wouldn't say the newbies
were nailing it yet.</i>

7
00:00:17.893 --> 00:00:20.103
<i>It's about being professional.</i>

8
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:27.652
<i>My doctor face had gotten
better and better over the years.</i>

9
00:00:27.653 --> 00:00:29.738
You've got something on your face. Asher.

10
00:00:30.989 --> 00:00:32.365
Looks like it's Amara.

11
00:00:32.366 --> 00:00:33.867
<i>Nothing could rattle me.</i>

12
00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:37.787
I'm not invited to the barbecue?
But it's our tradition.

13
00:00:37.788 --> 00:00:41.123
J.D.. we did it for 16 years.
That's hardly a tradition.

14
00:00:41.124 --> 00:00:44.043
Oh. really?
Then why did we record this last year?

15
00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:48.089
<i>♪ We're writing a prescription
For our barbecue tradition ♪</i>

16
00:00:48.090 --> 00:00:50.967
<i>♪ I'm already wishing
For next year's edition ♪</i>

17
00:00:50.968 --> 00:00:52.134
Harmony.

18
00:00:52.135 --> 00:00:55.179
<i>♪ Of our barbecue tradition ♪</i>

19
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:56.430
<i>♪ Tradition ♪</i>

20
00:00:56.431 --> 00:00:59.350
Okay. fine. Carla wants to do it
with Elliot and Wes this year.

21
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:00.685
You get it. buddy.

22
00:01:00.686 --> 00:01:02.520
Then you go to her. and you fight for me.

23
00:01:02.521 --> 00:01:05.940
I'm not strong enough. J.D.
She's going through menopause.

24
00:01:05.941 --> 00:01:08.442
She's having mood swings.
night sweats. day sweats.

25
00:01:08.443 --> 00:01:11.195
She's always wearing sweats.
I'm starting to avoid her.

26
00:01:11.196 --> 00:01:12.446
Hey. have you seen Turk?

27
00:01:12.447 --> 00:01:13.490
Yeah. he's right...

28
00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:17.077
I haven't seen him.

29
00:01:20.122 --> 00:01:23.416
Whoa. You just materialized.
You're like Merlin.

30
00:01:23.417 --> 00:01:24.709
I've gotten good.

31
00:01:24.710 --> 00:01:27.712
I see you. I ain't mad at the back either.

32
00:01:27.713 --> 00:01:29.046
Okay. Okay.

33
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:31.173
We're super excited
about the barbecue.

34
00:01:31.174 --> 00:01:34.218
Wes is bringing something
called a "Pilot's Booty."

35
00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:37.806
It's first-class warmed nuts
mixed with coach pretzels.

36
00:01:38.724 --> 00:01:40.141
Or you could just bring ice?

37
00:01:40.142 --> 00:01:43.894
We'll figure out something else to bring.
Save your "Pilot's Booty" for me.

38
00:01:43.895 --> 00:01:45.062
Okay. good night.

39
00:01:45.063 --> 00:01:46.315
Oh!

40
00:01:47.149 --> 00:01:48.399
Another hot flash?

41
00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:49.692
Just shut up and fan me.

42
00:01:49.693 --> 00:01:51.861
<i>I guess Carla wanted
to hide her menopause.</i>

43
00:01:51.862 --> 00:01:53.321
<i>but it wasn't going to be easy.</i>

44
00:01:55.991 --> 00:01:59.161
Doctor faces. everyone. doctor faces.

45
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:03.664
<i>♪ I can't do this all on my own ♪</i>

46
00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:07.252
<i>♪ No. I know I'm no Superman ♪</i>

47
00:02:10.464 --> 00:02:12.382
<i>♪ I'm no Superman ♪</i>

48
00:02:12.966 --> 00:02:15.259
I've been thinking. we should spend
more time together. you know?

49
00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.219
Really water the garden of our friendship.

50
00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:19.013
You're not coming to the barbecue. J.D.

51
00:02:19.014 --> 00:02:20.222
Oh. is that happening?

52
00:02:20.223 --> 00:02:22.266
Our long-standing tradition
of smoking meat

53
00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:24.518
and making memories that last a lifetime?

54
00:02:24.519 --> 00:02:26.188
I wasn't even thinking about it.

55
00:02:26.688 --> 00:02:30.107
Seriously. it's not about that.
I just... I miss you.

56
00:02:30.108 --> 00:02:33.110
Don't be sweet with me right now.
I can't handle it.

57
00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:35.280
- Okay. it's all good. Okay.
- Don't touch me.

58
00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:40.576
Mr. Butler. I'm Dr. Dorian...

59
00:02:40.577 --> 00:02:42.161
I'm sorry. is that ranch dressing?

60
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.538
I brought my own from home.
I'm kind of a ranch snob.

61
00:02:44.539 --> 00:02:48.250
Mr. Butler. if you don't make
some serious lifestyle changes.

62
00:02:48.251 --> 00:02:51.128
you're gonna suffer through
bypass surgery for no reason.

63
00:02:51.129 --> 00:02:54.548
But I am making lifestyle changes.
I take vitamins every day.

64
00:02:54.549 --> 00:02:56.050
I walk every day.

65
00:02:56.051 --> 00:02:57.760
I'm down to a jug a week.
I'm putting in the work.

66
00:02:57.761 --> 00:03:00.429
Listen. I know
making lifestyle changes is hard.

67
00:03:00.430 --> 00:03:02.682
but we're going to take this
one step at a time.

68
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:05.226
- Somethi<i>ng just as important...
- We c</i>an start with your beverages...

69
00:03:05.227 --> 00:03:08.939
...as <i>doctor face is nurse voice.
And Carla was the best.</i>

70
00:03:10.482 --> 00:03:13.193
Guys. we did everything we could.
This was a high-risk case.

71
00:03:13.902 --> 00:03:15.987
Yeah. but that doesn't make
telling the family any easier.

72
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:19.156
And yet. you are so good at it.

73
00:03:19.157 --> 00:03:21.117
Actually. Dashana. you're gonna be the one

74
00:03:21.118 --> 00:03:23.035
to tell the Garcia family
that he passed away.

75
00:03:23.036 --> 00:03:25.913
Oh. come on. man.
Now. you know I'm not good at this.

76
00:03:25.914 --> 00:03:28.208
Hey. other people's feelings
just bring up a lotta...

77
00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:30.084
You know?

78
00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:31.545
- Feelings?
- Yes!

79
00:03:32.504 --> 00:03:33.921
Look. I'm not a crier. okay?

80
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.339
- I'm not even a hugger.
- Oh.

81
00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:38.217
Even in high school basketball.
my coach told me to. "Bring it in."

82
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:39.301
Never did.

83
00:03:40.804 --> 00:03:42.263
Well. you're just like me.

84
00:03:42.264 --> 00:03:44.140
Hey! Come on. twin.

85
00:03:44.141 --> 00:03:46.767
No. No. it was a bad thing.
I needed to work on it and so do you.

86
00:03:46.768 --> 00:03:48.727
Look. that family is hurting.

87
00:03:48.728 --> 00:03:50.730
You need to step up and be there for them...

88
00:03:55.277 --> 00:03:56.486
because that's the job.

89
00:03:59.281 --> 00:04:02.158
<i>Even some of the old pros
could struggle with doctor face.</i>

90
00:04:02.159 --> 00:04:04.286
I am Mariah Carey.

91
00:04:05.370 --> 00:04:06.496
Don't look at me!

92
00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:10.082
<i>But Elliot had other things
on her mind.</i>

93
00:04:10.083 --> 00:04:13.711
Carla.
Wes just texted the funniest thing.

94
00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:15.171
<i>It was not funny.</i>

95
00:04:15.172 --> 00:04:18.340
All right. yeah. I get it.
"Cockpit" means two things.

96
00:04:18.341 --> 00:04:19.885
Classic. right?

97
00:04:20.510 --> 00:04:22.470
Wait. do you not like him?

98
00:04:22.471 --> 00:04:25.932
I mean. I don't really know him yet.
but I'm sure he's perfectly fine.

99
00:04:27.476 --> 00:04:30.395
<i>Elliot's relationship
wasn't the only one under scrutiny.</i>

100
00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:37.527
I really do need some gauze. Sorry.

101
00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:40.614
Bye.

102
00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:44.284
Okay. Anytime you have a hot flash.

103
00:04:45.577 --> 00:04:48.288
ice cream in the morgue is our new go-to.

104
00:04:49.664 --> 00:04:51.999
I'm just glad you're finally
talking about "the change."

105
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.294
Call it that one more time. you're gonna
find yourself in one of those drawers.

106
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:56.587
I'm not Teen Wolf.

107
00:04:56.588 --> 00:04:58.590
<i>Carla as Teen Wolf?</i>

108
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:01.092
<i>Don't get distracted. She needs you.</i>

109
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:04.512
Hey. tell me. What's been going on?

110
00:05:04.513 --> 00:05:06.138
Ugh!

111
00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:08.557
It's been so hard. J.D.

112
00:05:08.558 --> 00:05:13.521
I'm anxious. I'm moody. I can't sleep.
I'm finding hair in the strangest places.

113
00:05:13.522 --> 00:05:15.023
I'll bet you are.

114
00:05:15.649 --> 00:05:16.817
- Hey!
- Sorry!

115
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.151
You know what really sucks?

116
00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:21.779
I'm doing everything that I used to
at home and at work.

117
00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:23.740
- I always feel like I'm coming up short.
- Mm-hmm.

118
00:05:25.450 --> 00:05:26.534
I hate aging.

119
00:05:26.535 --> 00:05:28.410
Well. if it makes you feel any better.

120
00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:31.289
the only thing longer
than my father's earlobes...

121
00:05:31.957 --> 00:05:33.124
were his testicles.

122
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:35.627
So I've got that coming for me.

123
00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:37.837
You know. that does make me feel better.

124
00:05:38.964 --> 00:05:40.798
Please don't make me do this.

125
00:05:40.799 --> 00:05:43.134
I wanna cut stuff.
but not talk to families.

126
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:45.219
I'll just be a butcher.

127
00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:46.720
Dashana. I'm gonna give you some advice

128
00:05:46.721 --> 00:05:50.224
that's gotten me
through some really hard times.

129
00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:53.644
"The only way to grow
is to face challenges

130
00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:55.688
that seem beyond your strength."

131
00:05:55.689 --> 00:05:57.731
That's on the poster behind me. isn't it?

132
00:05:57.732 --> 00:06:00.443
It is. Put your doctor face on
and get in there.

133
00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:05.698
Um...

134
00:06:05.699 --> 00:06:08.869
Mrs. Garcia. I am so sorry.

135
00:06:09.494 --> 00:06:12.956
We did everything we could.
Your husband didn't make it.

136
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:16.835
It's just so hard.

137
00:06:17.460 --> 00:06:18.669
He worked all the time.

138
00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:21.131
- He was such a good dad.
- Oh...

139
00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:27.511
It feels like you guys could just...
hug each other now?

140
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:31.390
No. No. no. no.
You guys are in great hands.

141
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:32.934
Take all the time you need.

142
00:06:33.643 --> 00:06:35.186
Mmm.

143
00:06:40.942 --> 00:06:43.987
<i>For some reason.
Amara really reminded me of myself.</i>

144
00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:52.202
- Give me a hug.
- Uh-uh.

145
00:06:52.203 --> 00:06:54.496
Let me guess.
you've been kissing Asher again.

146
00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:56.373
It's the craziest thing I've ever done.

147
00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:59.209
And now that I've got a taste
of this crazy-girl lifestyle. I want more.

148
00:06:59.210 --> 00:07:02.880
I wanna try sushi. pole dancing.
I wanna flash a trucker. And--

149
00:07:02.881 --> 00:07:07.176
Okay. look. I love this for you.
but you still live with your aunt.

150
00:07:07.177 --> 00:07:09.887
so you might wanna stay off the pole.

151
00:07:09.888 --> 00:07:11.930
Maybe try going out with us
on a Saturday night

152
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:14.516
instead of making pasta and watching
<i>The Great British Bake Off</i> with her.

153
00:07:14.517 --> 00:07:16.977
You're right.
We're going out on Saturday night.

154
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:18.771
- <i>♪ We're going out on Saturday night ♪
-</i> Oh. my God.

155
00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:20.272
- <i>♪ We're going out on Saturday night ♪</i>
- Ay!

156
00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.899
<i>♪ We're going out on Saturday night ♪</i>

157
00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:23.109
So...

158
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.236
Shades inside. huh? Cool.

159
00:07:26.237 --> 00:07:29.658
Looks like we're gonna get you started
on IV antibiotics for your cellulitis.

160
00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:34.496
What you are going to get started on
is this list.

161
00:07:36.081 --> 00:07:38.083
And this dressing room is unacceptable.

162
00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:43.003
Baby. you was falling asleep again.

163
00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:46.465
Again? What does that mean. "again"?
You're always saying again.

164
00:07:46.466 --> 00:07:48.300
Nah. nah. I just be talking sometimes.

165
00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:50.135
I have an energy-boost smoothie

166
00:07:50.136 --> 00:07:53.055
for the hardest-working woman
in the hospital.

167
00:07:53.056 --> 00:07:55.349
I call it "the mangopause."

168
00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:59.104
- That's funny.
- Yeah. So funny.

169
00:07:59.646 --> 00:08:01.980
I gotta get some more napkins
for my armpits.

170
00:08:01.981 --> 00:08:03.274
Okay.

171
00:08:04.150 --> 00:08:06.110
Would you like to borrow
some of my thunder

172
00:08:06.111 --> 00:08:07.486
since I stole all of yours?

173
00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:09.238
J.D.. I'ma tell you something right now.

174
00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:11.824
You sound like that guy who went
to go live with the grizzly bears.

175
00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.493
At first he was like.
"I'm the grizzly man. They love me."

176
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:15.869
And then one day. they tore his ass up.

177
00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:17.872
Don't hate me
just because I understand women.

178
00:08:18.540 --> 00:08:22.209
You know. I should really teach a course
for less enlightened guys like you.

179
00:08:22.210 --> 00:08:24.670
I could call it. "Hey. man. pause."

180
00:08:25.755 --> 00:08:26.839
- Turk.
- Hey.

181
00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:30.592
You can still eat sweet barbecue sauce
with your diabetes. right?

182
00:08:30.593 --> 00:08:32.970
Yeah. I mean. I got my 'pod.

183
00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:35.097
I can dose insulin from my phone
for any meal I want.

184
00:08:35.098 --> 00:08:37.433
- Then we have some big news.
- Okay.

185
00:08:37.434 --> 00:08:40.060
Wes is flying a pair of lungs
to save a smoker in Kansas City--

186
00:08:40.061 --> 00:08:44.064
And then I'm stopping at a smoker
in Kansas City to pick you up...

187
00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:45.649
the best brisket in the country.

188
00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:50.029
Wow. that's-- that's really nice.
Wow. Thank you. Wes.

189
00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:51.113
It's okay. Turk.

190
00:08:51.114 --> 00:08:53.700
You can be happy even though
I'm not invited to the barbecue.

191
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:57.286
Kansas City brisket. here we come!
Let's go!

192
00:08:57.287 --> 00:09:02.000
<i>I'm gonna put a hex on his belly.
Where is my witchcraft workbook?</i>

193
00:09:02.917 --> 00:09:04.960
So. Turk seemed excited.

194
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:06.921
Most meat makes Turk excited.

195
00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:10.550
Three of our daughters are because
they kept bringing back the McRib.

196
00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:13.552
Carla. do you like Wes or not?

197
00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:17.222
Honestly. I thought your first fling
would be a lot more exciting.

198
00:09:17.223 --> 00:09:19.975
He flies a plane. In the sky.

199
00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:23.438
Yeah. You'd think
that'd be more interesting. Hmm.

200
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.650
I have something to show you
behind this curtain.

201
00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:34.948
So when I told my dad about us.
he said that when you really like someone.

202
00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:37.327
you should do something for them
every day to let them know.

203
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:39.788
His name is Asher Bear.

204
00:09:41.206 --> 00:09:42.873
You told your dad about us?

205
00:09:42.874 --> 00:09:44.792
- Mm-hmm.
- It's been less than a week.

206
00:09:44.793 --> 00:09:47.044
We haven't even made out
in real clothes yet.

207
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.505
Well. that's long enough for me
to know how I feel about you.

208
00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:51.007
Yeah. yeah.

209
00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:53.175
Yet when I visualized this moment.

210
00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:55.135
there was more kissing
and less backing away.

211
00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:56.387
That sounds...

212
00:09:57.347 --> 00:09:58.848
Yeah. yeah.

213
00:10:00.642 --> 00:10:03.811
When you open your locker.
there may be an eruption of flowers.

214
00:10:03.812 --> 00:10:05.187
Please disregard.

215
00:10:05.188 --> 00:10:09.818
Dashana. I'm gonna be honest with you.
You failed the Garcia family big time.

216
00:10:10.401 --> 00:10:12.486
But good news. you get to retake the test.

217
00:10:12.487 --> 00:10:15.614
Okay. retake the test?
Mrs. Garcia knows he's dead.

218
00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:17.116
I made that very clear.

219
00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:18.909
Remember when the Garcia family was saying

220
00:10:18.910 --> 00:10:21.161
- how he was always away working?
- Yeah.

221
00:10:21.162 --> 00:10:25.415
Yeah. what he was working on
was hiding his second family.

222
00:10:25.416 --> 00:10:27.251
Ooh. second family.

223
00:10:27.252 --> 00:10:29.211
This is my favorite kind
of hospital gossip.

224
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:31.547
second only to when the baby
come out the wrong color.

225
00:10:31.548 --> 00:10:33.423
Mmm!

226
00:10:33.424 --> 00:10:35.259
Oh. God. I cannot believe this.

227
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:38.429
Me neither. Mr. Garcia was not cute.

228
00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:43.351
Fresh flowers. fruit bowl. Perrier.
Who does she think she is?

229
00:10:43.935 --> 00:10:46.478
Mariah Carey. She was very clear.

230
00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:50.316
She suffers from psychosis. Blake.
You got to treat the whole patient.

231
00:10:50.942 --> 00:10:54.070
Even if that means
supporting some of her delusions.

232
00:10:55.155 --> 00:10:56.739
What... How am I supposed to do that?

233
00:10:58.116 --> 00:11:01.910
Look. Blake. you're the best intern
in this place.

234
00:11:01.911 --> 00:11:03.078
You'll figure it out.

235
00:11:03.079 --> 00:11:05.581
Wow. the best? Really?

236
00:11:05.582 --> 00:11:09.668
Ha! See how good that made you feel?
Support the delusion.

237
00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:12.754
Being kind is
part of being the best. Blake.

238
00:11:15.758 --> 00:11:17.468
How come I only have two patients?

239
00:11:18.011 --> 00:11:20.721
Oh! Child. Dr. Dorian asked us
to cut your workload

240
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:22.681
- into what you can handle.
- We got you. baby.

241
